1. These Rules may be cited as the Detention Camps (Discipline) Rules.
2. In these Rules, except where the context otherwise requires -
"Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Prisons;

(a) admonition ;
(b) reprimand or severe reprimand ;
(c) confinement to lines and extra duty ;
(d) fine not exceeding ten shillings ;
(e) stoppage of pay where there has been loss by neglect of or
injury to Government property, or absence without leave ;
(f) forfeiture of one good conduct badge;
(g) reduction in grade ;
(h) dismissal ;
(i) any two or more of the above punishments:

foreign.xhtml:div:
2.In this Act, except where a contrary intention appears -
"court" includes a judge of the High Court;
"detainee" means any person, whether convicted or not, lawfully detained in a detention camp;
"detention camp" means any place established in accordance with this Act in which prisoners may serve a term of detention in lieu of serving a term of imprisonment;
"officer in charge" means any officer appointed by name or office to have charge of a detention camp*.
_____________________________________________________________
*Where the officer in charge is a District Commissioner, his powers and duties shall be exercised and performed, during any period of absence or inability to act from illness or any other cause, by any District Officer for the time being serving in the district in which the detention camp is situate. (Cap 80 (1948), Sub. Leg.)
